<topic topic-id="DHPSSOIntegration" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions">
  <title>HP SSO Integration</title>
  <source>/120814-042457/Help/en/topics/DHPSSOIntegration.xml</source>
  <keywords>HP SSO Integration</keywords>
  <intro />
  <sections>
    <section>
      <desc />
      <content>
        <p class="bodytext">HP BladeSystem Onboard Administrator supports SSO with trusted applications, such as HP OneView or HP SIM. The HP SSO feature enables you to log in to a trusted management application and then to access automatically any managed devices where the SSO certificate is installed.</p>
        <p class="bodytext">
          <b>Settings tab</b>
        </p>
        <p class="bodytext">
          <b>HP SSO Trust Mode</b>
        </p>
        <p class="tablespacerbefore" />
        <table width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
          <tr>
            <th class="tableheading" style="border:1px solid #010101;text-align:left;">Trust mode
</th>
            <th class="tableheading" style="border:1px solid #010101;text-align:left;">Description
</th>
          </tr>
          <tr valign="top">
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">Disabled
</p>
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">SSO validation is disabled
</p>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr valign="top">
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">Trust By Certificate
</p>
            </td>
            <td style="border:1px solid #010101;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">Allow SSO using only HP management server certificates
</p>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        <p class="alertspacerbefore" />
        <table width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" rowsep="0" colsep="0">
          <tr valign="top">
            <td style="border:0px;width:1%;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext"></p>
            </td>
            <td style="border-top:1px solid #0066FF;border-right:0px;border-bottom:1px solid #0066FF;border-left:0px;" align="left">
              <p class="tablebodytext">
                <b style="color:#0066FF;">NOTE:</b>  When trust mode is disabled, the HP SSO single sign-on attempt fails. To log on, you must enter Onboard Administrator credentials.
</p>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        <p class="alertspacerafter" />
        <p class="bodytext">Select a trust mode, then click <b>Apply.</b></p>
      </content>
    </section>
  </sections>
</topic>